{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The gap between the requirements elicitation engineers and the customers/users is mainly attributed to the distance between diverse professional and team cultures, but in GSE also distance in national and organization cultures of involved stakeholders (Siakas et al. 2016).",
    "This gap propagates the problems towards modelling/specification design and implementation of the final product, and finally may end up in the production of a system which does not meet customer needs and requirements (Damian and Zowghi 2003).",
    "Despite the importance of requirements elicitation and the problems caused by an inability to understand and meet customer/user requirements (Dijksta 1972; Alsanoosy et al. 2018), insufficient attention has been paid to this area in Software Engineering (SE) research.",
    "Basic semantic differences in viewpoints may also exist when attempting to engage in meaningful dialogue between the problem owning and the problem-solving communities (Bostrum 1989).",
    "Requirements elicitation activities increase in significance when the \"culture gap\" between software developers and users is considered (Furxhi 2021)."
  ],
